defs.docs:
Compile time optimized maps and sets.

 PHF data structures can be generated via the syntax extensions in the
 `phf_macros` crate or via code generation in the `phf_codegen` crate. See
 the documentation of those crates for more details.

defs.name: map
defs.docs: An immutable map constructed at compile time.

defs.name: Map
defs.docs:
An immutable map constructed at compile time.

 ## Note

 The fields of this struct are public so that they may be initialized by the
 `phf_map!` macro and code generation. They are subject to change at any
 time and should never be accessed directly.

defs.name: Entries
defs.docs: An iterator over the key/value pairs in a `Map`.

defs.name: Keys
defs.docs: An iterator over the keys in a `Map`.

defs.name: Values
defs.docs: An iterator over the values in a `Map`.

defs.name: set
defs.docs: An immutable set constructed at compile time.

defs.name: Set
defs.docs:
An immutable set constructed at compile time.

 ## Note

 The fields of this struct are public so that they may be initialized by the
 `phf_set!` macro and code generation. They are subject to change at any
 time and should never be accessed directly.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over the values in a `Set`.

defs.name: ordered_map
defs.docs: An order-preserving immutable map constructed at compile time.

defs.name: OrderedMap
defs.docs:
An order-preserving immutable map constructed at compile time.

 Unlike a `Map`, iteration order is guaranteed to match the definition
 order.

 ## Note

 The fields of this struct are public so that they may be initialized by the
 `phf_ordered_map!` macro and code generation. They are subject to change at
 any time and should never be accessed directly.

defs.name: Entries
defs.docs: An iterator over the entries in a `OrderedMap`.

defs.name: Keys
defs.docs: An iterator over the keys in a `OrderedMap`.

defs.name: Values
defs.docs: An iterator over the values in a `OrderedMap`.

defs.name: ordered_set
defs.docs: An order-preserving immutable set constructed at compile time.
